# Voice Announcements Documentation

When modifying files in `packages/announcements/`, the documentation at `docs/ANNOUNCEMENTS.md` may need updates.

## Before Completing Changes

Review if your changes affect any of these documented areas:

| Area | What to Check |
|------|---------------|
| **Architecture** | New scripts, queue changes, flow modifications |
| **Services** | Script parameters, new scripts, renamed scripts |
| **Parameters** | New/changed parameters for `voice_announcement` or `critical_announcement` |
| **Smart Behaviors** | Time restrictions, mode interactions, volume logic |
| **Queue System** | MQTT topics, priority handling, expiration logic |
| **Sound Library** | New sounds, sound categories, person intros |
| **File Structure** | New files, renamed files, reorganized folders |

## Action Required

After making changes, ask the user:

> "I've modified the voice announcement system. Should I review and update `docs/ANNOUNCEMENTS.md` to reflect these changes?"

If the user agrees, read the current documentation and update any sections affected by the changes.
